# Coding Standards (Dart/Flutter)

## 1. Imports — Organization Rules

```dart
// GOOD: order: dart → package → relative, alphabetically sorted
import 'dart:async';
import 'dart:convert';

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';

import '../domain/verse_entity.dart';
import 'verse_repository.dart';

// BAD: mixed order, unused imports left behind
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import '../domain/verse_entity.dart';
import 'dart:async'; // dart import should be at the top
import 'package:unused_package/unused.dart'; // unused
```

## 2. Type Hints — Mandatory for all public APIs

```dart
// GOOD: explicit return and parameter types
Future<List<Verse>> getVerses({
  required int bookId,
  required int chapter,
}) async { ... }

// BAD: relying solely on type inference
getVerses(bookId, chapter) async { ... }
```

## 3. Null Safety — Prohibition of blind `!` operator

```dart
// GOOD: null-aware operators or explicit validation
final name = user?.displayName ?? 'Guest';

// BAD: overusing bang operator (!) → cause of runtime crashes
final name = user!.displayName!;
```

## 4. Immutability — No direct state mutation

```dart
// GOOD: create new object via copyWith (Freezed)
state = state.copyWith(isLoading: true);

// BAD: direct state mutation
state.isLoading = true; // PROHIBITED
```

## 5. Error Handling — No empty catch blocks

```dart
// GOOD: specific exception types + logging
try {
  await supabaseClient.from('verses').select();
} on PostgrestException catch (e) {
  _logger.severe('DB query failed: ${e.message}');
  rethrow;
}

// BAD: swallowing all exceptions in a catch
try {
  await supabaseClient.from('verses').select();
} catch (e) {
  // doing nothing → STRICTLY PROHIBITED
}
```

## 6. Widget Composition — Business Logic Separation

```dart
// GOOD: Widget only watches state and renders
class VerseScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final versesAsync = ref.watch(versesProvider);
    return versesAsync.when(
      data: (verses) => VerseList(verses: verses),
      loading: () => const LoadingIndicator(),
      error: (e, st) => ErrorDisplay(error: e),
    );
  }
}

// BAD: Direct DB calls inside Widget
class VerseScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  // ...
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    db.query('verses'); // PROHIBITED: direct DB call from Presentation layer
  }
}
```

## 7. No Magic Numbers/Strings

```dart
// GOOD: define constants
static const int maxRetries = 3;
static const Duration syncInterval = Duration(minutes: 5);

// BAD: ambiguous numbers/strings
await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 300)); // what is 300?
if (status == 'active') { ... } // 'active' should be a constant
```

